Our investigation has lead us to Kyurem, a Dragon- and Ice-type Pokémon.
The freezing energy Kyurem generates inside itself is so powerful that when it leaked out, it froze Kyurem's body solid.
Just thinking about it sends shivers down my spine...
So let's do some warm-ups, %PLAYERNAME%! We want to stay limber for the big day of exploring ahead of us.
There are rumors that Kyurem may dwell in the Unova region.
Unova is an extraordinary place. It has bustling, modern metropolises, but it's also home to tranquil forests where people live in harmony with nature.
And to confront a mystery discovered in Unova, it's only fitting we get help from Pokémon discovered in Unova too.
Which of these first partner Pokémon would you choose for this adventure?
The shell on Oshawott's body is called its "scalchop."
Oshawott uses its scalchop not only as a blade in battle but also as a tool to break open hard Berries.
It sharpens it on riverbed stones, just like a human with a whetstone.
A perfect-sized shell and stone are just some of Oshawott's unique needs.
I bet Kyurem has unique needs too... While you train your new partner, I'll study Kyurem to find out what it wants.
Snivy avoids groups, so it's a great match for Trainers who are more independent.
It uses its tail to photosynthesize sunlight. If Snivy's not feeling well, its tail will start to droop.
On the other hand — or vine! — Snivy who are full of energy become swift and dexterous.
Alone time and ample sunlight are just some of Snivy's unique needs.
I bet Kyurem has unique needs too... While you train your new partner, I'll study Kyurem to find out what it wants.
Make sure you have plenty of Berries on hand when you go adventuring with Tepig!
Tepig loves to roast its food, but sometimes it gets too excited and burns its meal to a crisp.
It shoots fireballs from its nose, but if it's feeling ill, that fire turns to pitch-black smoke.
Snacks aplenty is just one of Tepig's unique needs.
I bet Kyurem has unique needs too... While you train your new partner, I'll study Kyurem to find out what it wants.
Kyurem seems to be looking for something...
According to my research, it's waiting for a hero to fill in the missing parts of its body with either truth or ideals.
I wonder what that means? While you're certainly my hero, %PLAYERNAME%, we don't fully understand the mystery of truth and ideals.
The best we can do for now is slow Kyurem down. Battle Kyurem with all your different strengths, and you're sure to succeed!x
What an inspiring battle! When people and Pokémon work together, we can achieve our greatest dreams, overcoming our differences.
Oshawott looks like it learned a lot from you too. Why, I think it's ready to evolve!
Enjoy your adventure now, %PLAYERNAME%. This won't the last we've seen of Kyurem, but you averted disaster by defeating it today.
What an inspiring battle! When people and Pokémon work together, we can achieve our greatest dreams, overcoming our differences.
Snivy looks like it learned a lot from you too. Why, I think it's ready to evolve!
Enjoy your adventure now, %PLAYERNAME%. This won't the last we've seen of Kyurem, but you averted disaster by defeating it today.
What an inspiring battle! When people and Pokémon work together, we can achieve our greatest dreams, overcoming our differences.
Tepig looks like it learned a lot from you too. Why, I think it's ready to evolve!
Enjoy your adventure now, %PLAYERNAME%. This won't the last we've seen of Kyurem, but you averted disaster by defeating it today.
Hey there, %PLAYERNAME%! Funny you should pop by—I was just reflecting on our incredible journey together!
Encountering gigantic Pokémon, unfurling incredible mysteries, foiling Team GO Rocket countless times... We’ve faced extraordinary challenges together, haven’t we?
Our research has introduced us to Pokémon from all over the world, forged wonderful friendships, and led to some amazing discoveries.
And speaking of discoveries, I’ve noticed some unusual sounds lately.
I’m going to investigate, and while I do, I need you to continue your excellent work in the field.
Good news, %PLAYERNAME%! I’ve made a breakthrough on those acoustic mysteries I was looking into.
And as I suspected, they’re not just any sound wave, they’re the unique melodies of the Mythical Pokémon Meloetta!
Meloetta uses song to influence the emotions of those who hear it. And on that note, I’d like you to try and spot any unusual behavior in the local Pokémon.
It’s not every day we get to study a Mythical Pokémon, so let’s make the most of this opportunity!
Hello again, %PLAYERNAME%! We may not have found Meloetta yet, but I can definitely still hear it.
So our musical friend can’t be too far off—we just might have to change our usual pitch.
Why don’t you go out and do a little singing and dancing to see if it affects people and Pokémon nearby?
Who knows, that might be the "key" to success! Heh heh... Music joke. I’ve got a million!
If it isn’t our intrepid enter-Trainer! Say, did you know that Meloetta’s melodies have inspired many famous songs?
It’s just fascinating—Meloetta shows us how music helps us to forge special bonds with one another.
It’s not unlike your amazing ability to connect with other people and Pokémon. Every new Pokémon you catch or Trainer you meet is a new potential friend!
And on that uplifting note, get out there and see what new friendships await, %PLAYERNAME%.
%PLAYERNAME%! I’ve dug up some useful information on Meloetta. Did you know that it was first discovered in the Unova region?
That might not seem critical, but we have to take advantage of every scrap of information we can to help us make sense of Meloetta’s behavior.
Keep up your fieldwork, if you would! Watch for Pokémon experiencing strong emotions, check out some new places, and maybe try to forge some new connections.
Let’s keep this research rhythm going!
This is the moment we’ve been waiting for, %PLAYERNAME%!
Your dedicated work has helped me to pinpoint Meloetta’s location at last!
This could be your chance to befriend an extraordinary Pokémon.
Head out there and show Meloetta the same kindness and dedication you’ve shown all your Pokémon friends!
What a striking appearance this Meloetta has! My research notes have nothing about this distinctive coloring. It’s truly incredible!
I’ve been watching your journey since you took your first steps as a Trainer. Seeing how far you’ve come makes me so proud to call you my research partner—and more importantly, my friend!
I know you’ll keep that Meloetta singing proudly, %PLAYERNAME%. You never fall flat!

La dualité dont nous avons été témoins a révélé les contrastes entre la nature de ce monde et ses occupants.
La dernière instance rencontrée m’intrigue particulièrement.
Blanche et Cliff recherchent l’innovation dans le combat, mais l’un d’entre eux a choisi la défense tandis que l’autre s’est tourné vers la poursuite du pouvoir.
J’aimerais regarder cela de plus près. Si tu veux bien m’excuser, je dois examiner ces découvertes avec le Professeur Willow.
Tu as plus d’expérience en combat que moi, %PLAYERNAME%, alors j’aimerais avoir ton opinion. Penses-tu qu’une approche équilibrée soit importante pour un Dresseur ou une Dresseuse Pokémon ?
Étonnant. C’est peut-être la clé pour comprendre ces évènements récents.
Il faut toujours voir les deux côtés d’une chose. Il est peu probable que de se focaliser sur un seul de ces aspects apporte de bons résultats.
Tournons-nous vers le futur. L’expérience suggère que l’on devrait bientôt recevoir des informations du Professeur au sujet de Candela ou sur le dernier chef de la Team GO Rocket.
Préparons-nous. En attendant, je crois qu’on dit « à la revoyure ».
Les dernières informations suggèrent que Cliff s’entraîne comme un forcené, et il aurait une nouvelle stratégie : attaquer, attaquer, attaquer.
De son côté, Blanche a fait une nouvelle découverte et souhaite cultiver les capacités des Pokémon dotés d’une puissante défense.
L’attaque et la défense, deux approches opposées mais complémentaires, comme la dernière fois. Je parie que nous pouvons en apprendre plus sur cette dualité si nous creusons un peu.
À ce propos, je t’invite à me dire laquelle de leurs stratégies tu souhaites découvrir plus en détail.
Salutations, %PLAYERNAME%. Ton aide sera la bienvenue.
Mes recherches m’ont amené à une conclusion : aussi évident que cela puisse paraître, le moyen le plus sûr de gagner un combat est de ne jamais le perdre.
En d’autres termes, si ton Pokémon n’est jamais mis K.O., la victoire est la seule issue possible.
Lokhlass et moi avons commencé à tester plusieurs méthodologies qui maximisent son potentiel de défense. Aimeriez-vous vous joindre à nous, toi et tes partenaires Pokémon ?
Hé, regarde où tu mets les pieds ! C’est là que je m’entraîne !
Les attaques à pleine puissance sur lesquelles je travaille rendront la Team GO Rocket inarrêtable. Pourquoi tu me regardes comme ça ? Tu ne me crois pas ?
C’est très simple. Tu fais en sorte que tes Pokémon frappent si fort que leurs adversaires n’ont même pas la CHANCE de riposter !
Enfin, ça ne te concerne pas. Je doute qu’une personne aussi faible que toi puisse réussir une telle attaque avec son Pokémon.
Et ça veut dire que tu vas freiner ma progression si tu restes dans les parages. Alors, du balai !
Félicitations pour ce travail bien fait.
Mon analyse des dernières batailles a réfuté ma théorie précédente, mais ce n’est pas de ta faute.
J’ai placé tous mes efforts sur la défense de Lokhlass et j’ai négligé de lui donner des occasions d’attaquer.
Je crains d’avoir freiné son développement. La suite logique est de lui donner des Baies, de le féliciter et, surtout, de lui donner un entraînement plus complet.
Nous devrions cependant prendre un peu de repos avant de repartir à l’action. %PLAYERNAME%, si tu m’as appris quelque chose aujourd’hui, c’est l’importance d’une approche équilibrée.
Hmm. La force règne en maître, mais il manque encore quelque chose !
Le problème quand on se concentre uniquement sur l’attaque, c’est qu’on baisse sa garde.
Peut-être que le boss préférerait que j’utilise l’attaque ET la défense...
Mais cela ne m’arrêtera pas ! Je maîtriserai le pouvoir de l’équilibre pour la Team GO Rocket, quoi qu’il m’en coûte !
